text:
We stayed at Pramana for 25 nights in 1 bedroom villa with a private pool, I can't complain about any of their services. We were amazed. The receptionists were very friendly and welcoming. The housekeeping staff of Made 3 did a very good job , they made sure our Villa was always clean, clean swimming pool and a neat bed. Let's not even talk about the food, I thought I would have a problem trying new recipes, but I didn't, yummy 😋, good presentations. Waiters and waitresses were very friendly and offered us their best. There was this one in particular that we can't forget of, "Inyoman Darmayasa from the restaurant". That boy is very good at his job. 
It was my 1st vacation to Bali, I was scared at first of the rumors I have heard about Bali, but all I can say now is that, it was worth going, a very good experience indeed, especially when you book the right Hotel for your vacation. 25 nights was like 1 week there, it went so quick that we didn't feel like checking out😒.
As someone who knows a lot about hospitality and works in a 5 star Hotel as a supervisor, I can only say that their 1st impression proved it all, "as for me", I can say it's one of the best  peaceful , comfortable and very private Hotel villa  to stay for your vacation in Bali. The location is right near the beach with a nice restaurant on the beach 😍. Oh!,  did you know they offer free shuttle to take you around the Hotel?😜,very helpful drivers, they won't ask you for money 😀, that's something we don't have in my Country, not for free, you pay. You should give it a try😊.
Being a supervisor, they  didn't know I was taking notes, I was impressed,  I never told them about my career until my love blew my cover 2 days to our check out 🙄. "He just couldn't zip it till the last day, he likes showing me off".... Big up Desa Pramana for making our vacation fabulous 👍👌. Looking forward to come back someday 🙏.
title: Comfort and peaceful Villa to cool off.

text:
I am so sorry for this negative feedback because villas and staff are great!
But the position is really bad just in The middle of nowhere.
It is impossible to have a walk because there is only a sort of highway without sidewalk and you risk your life.
It is impossible to go to the seaside because the waves are Very high and it is dangerous to have a bath and the Sand is Very short so you cannot put your towel to have a sunbath.
Even the restaurant is so bad, for example fruit and fruit juices are not delicious as expected in a country Like Indonesia. This is a very pity. The breakfast included is Very poor and if you ask something more or different you have to Pay. Also the breakfast box is quite embarassing just 2 slides of toasted bread + small banana + 2 small croissant + 1 small water bottle.
On the other hand villas are huge and comfortable and you have private pool. But a bad point is that you have only 2 towels even if you are in 4 people and you should ask for more every day.
Staff is Very kindly.

text: We had a villa and a private pool all to ourselves as the other 2 villas were vacant during our 3 nights stay. It was lovely to have the privacy. However it rained mostly the first 2 days and the villa restaurant is about 5 minutes walk away also the beach. Not close to shops or other restaurants, We had to hire a motorbike to get us around. Otherwise the facilities of the villa are good. TV reception is poor and only has local stations.

text: We'd had a reservation 4.5km further up the road, and on arrival found nothing matched the website propaganda. Including not having a private pool, or any pool. After staying 1 night out of the 3 we moved out and came to Swan. On speaking to management they offered us a fantastic price for a large fully equipped very private villa, so were able to be joined by our friends on the 2nd night. With our own private pool, outdoor seating, nothing was too much trouble. Staff organised motor bikes, laundry, all at excellent prices - they were so sweet. The 2 level villa was spotless and so fresh after our bad experience down the road, Swan delivered everything as promised. The restaurant was adequate - we ate all our meals here and the included breakfast was also good enough. There was excellent security at this gated establishment. Thank you to all the great folk at Swan for saving our stay in Keramas.
title: Loved our stay!

text: I stayed with my partner for 10 days from the minute we arrived at the resort our overall experience with the staff, villa and food was flawless and way beyond expectations. We have travelled overseas and within our own country Australia and have never received such welcoming, professional and excellent service from any hotel, resort or staycation we have been to. We had a private villa that was cleaned at our request and was done to the perfection as if we had just arrived on our first day. All the staff were welcoming, engaging and very lovely to talk to. The food was at the breakfast buffet was great but warm to cold, which considering the weather was not too bothered by the coldish food. The lunch and dinner meals were flavoursome and a great Balinese taste. The restaurant was very accommodating to our tastes and even supplied a new meal when not cooked to our liking. They also replaced a drink that was not appetising even though I said nothing just put the drink to the side. Our overall holiday and stay is 9.5 and the lost .5 was because it would have been nice to have a courtesy airport shuttle to and from as the cost in total was 800 000 return which could have been used on drinks.
title: The best holiday experience to date!

text: Just had a wonderful 2 week stay. The Villas are very spacious and very clean and we loved the location, just a 2/3 min walk to the beach restaurant. The customer service here is very impressive, I suffered a bad foot cut whilst surfing and the Villa staff were frankly amazing, they provided prompt first aid and whisked me to hospital so I could be stitched up. The resort manager even visited us in hospital and arranged for a full breakfast to be delivered to us…..then they delivered flowers to our villa! Most amazing customer service we have experience. We also have to profusely thank our driver Maddy, he took us all over the island and shower us many sights we would have missed, he’s a real credit to the team and was so much fun to be around. Were sad to be leaving but we will certainly be returning.
title: Amazing villa with 5* hotel service

text: Location is excellent, close to the beach. Our villa had a main building with dining area, sitting room and kitchen and bedroom, en-suite on the first floor. Also 2 other buildings with Bedroom and en-suite were included. There was an immaculate private pool in the garden with sun beds with Parasol. The staff are very helpful and friendly. The resort has its own Massage Salon as well. The restaurant is great not just for breakfast but for lunch and dinner as well and is located right on the beach about a 7 minute walk or the resort can supply shuttle service  to and from the restaurant. The owners as well as many other businesses are all trying to recover after the Covid so one should expect that some things could be improved but everybody is trying very hard and we, the tourist , should give them a bit of time and leeway. I highly recommend this "Diamond of Keramas", a very quiet place to recover from the hustle and bustle of the rest of Bali, as we could not fault the resort

We had an amazing time at Pramana Swan. Highly recommend the massages at the spa. The villas have individual swimming pool and traditional wood and natural materials for the furniture. Communication with reception is made easy by WhatsApp. 
They offer buggy service for free when is raining and there are taxi, car rent / scooter rent on the property. 
Having visited many beaches in Bali, it is fair to say the black beach in Keramas is one of the top ones, easy to walk, very long, clean and authentic. You can see stone pickers when the tide is low. Occasionally, when the water is calmer is possible to swim. There are many restaurants and bars by the beach which you can reach by foot, we recommend Komune hotel. 
Points to improve: more sockets in the room, for e.g for the kettle and to charge the mobile phones

text:
At DPS as they try really hard to make your stay as nice as possible, the staff go way over and above what you'd expect and nothing is any trouble for them.

We had 12 nights here and barring the long way (20 hours) and the awful 3 hours to get through the airport upon arrival we wouldn't hesitate to go back. DPS is about 45(?) mins from the airport and can that vary widely with traffic volumes. DPS can pick you up for a fee.

The villa was lovely. Our unit had 3 double bedroom and a sitting/sitting/dining (come anything) room that is huge. Because we were only one couple 2 rooms were locked offering us complete privacy to our room, lounge / dining, kitchen and a lovely private pool. The private garden around us allowed us to lock the gate and the staff then ring a bell to be let in for e.g. room service. The villas are along a road and don't overlook each other. Ours was a 15 minute walk to the beach and restaurant. Higher room numbers are closer to the restaurant/beach. We were in Vila 9 and were next to the spa and massage rooms. The massages are lovely with an hour of relaxation by people who seem to know what they are doing.  We went a couple of times. Very nice!

Communications are easy as you are soon contacted by WhatsApp through your free villa WiFi . You even get the restaurant menu through it on arrival. WIFI is strong enough to stream TV. Standard TV has BBC news in English.  5 channels were local. You may not go to such a lovely place to watch TV :) but my Firestick worked fabulously.

Room service is 30 mins to an hour I guess, and it's a strange site to see a petit lady on the back of a moped balancing this huge tray of room service on her head. Occasionally you may want to use the microwave to heat it back up a bit. No delivery charge.  Room service breakfast have items not available in the buffet.  No idea why.

I damaged my knee when there so I was not only taken to and brought back from the hospital by DPS, they even found, ordered and had delivered a pair of crutches for me and it all went on my bill - no overcharging.

The breakfast has most things and is buffet style. From bacon, eggs, more native style foods as in noodles, cooked veg type and maybe sweet/sour chicken , fruit, bakery. You'd have to be a fuss pot to miss out.

The only restaurant serves nice value for money food, well cooked and presented. Wine is rather expensive.  Local BINTANG beer, not so much. Salad portions are small. We had a couple of occasions where items weren't available but there's a long list of things that are and it’s all very tasty.  There is a winery across the busy dual carriage road who accepts cards.  Grocery shops sell beer.

The restaurant couldn't be closer to the beach. Warm, black sand, that sparkles in torchlight. Surfers try out the waves before they crash against the shore – all very beautiful.  Swimming is prohibited by a single sign “due to strong currents”.  Playing in the waves is very possible at some times of the day.

There's not a lot they could improve here and I'm still praising the staff, a proactive happy lot who always want to say 'hello' and help if they can. Even the mozzies are few and far between.

General comments
- wherever we went we found wine to be very expensive. We got the impression that there must be a high import tax on wine as its cost seems to be pervasive everywhere.
- this is a quieter area of the island.
- If you're going to book through B.com (this site) then phone DSP direct - we literally halved the price by doing so.
- (Covid) We flew Emirates who at Larnaca (Cyprus), our departure point, were insisting we download an App to be filled in before we could receive our Boarding Passes. Most of this App is in Indonesian and we spent our 3 hours waiting time trying to figure it out with no help and no success.  Eventually we were given our passes as they had loaded our luggage... and told to sort it out in Dubai.  We essentially ignored this as we had also received our onward Boarding Passes. At Denpasar, our Vaccination Certificates were given a passing glance and the stress ended. Rarely do the locals wear masks and nobody asked for our Covid paperwork once through the airport, even at the hospital.

This is a quiet area of Bali and shopping for your villa kitchen is not easy.  Small Grocery Shops only accept cash so get cash at the airport.  If you can stop on the way from the airport for the essentials it will serve you well.  There are a few good restaurants via a walk on the beach.
title: A thoroughly enjoyable time

text: The Villa is absolutely beautiful. Privacy was our main concern and we got it. The pool is fairly large and up to 1,25 M deep. Super comfy beds, hot water, free delicious breakfast, super clean. There's a market within walking distance from the villas, just make sure you use the crosswalk, and be careful. Traffic isn't slowing down for you. The black sand beach is also a short walk. Which is also where the restaurant is located. Absolutely delicious food. Not too greasy but full of flavor. Every room can be enclosed but the living room does not have AC. It wasn't needed as the whether was excellent just opening the sliding door offers a nice breeze. There's AC where it matters (in the bedroom). We had a few critters. The staff was quick in removing them. Remember that these are Hindu people who prefer not to kill even insects. So expect a bug or 2, no big deal. There's also a taxi crew situated right next to the villas that will take you wherever you want to go, they also served as guides and translators to some extent. We're extremely satisfied with our trip, and will likely be sending our parents to the same villa in the future.
title: Exactly what we hoped for

text:
We loved every thing about this place !!

The Villas are same as published in internet and in fact more beautiful than in pictures. The restaurant on the black sand beach is Heaven just to sit by ,relax ,feel the breeze, listening to rhythm of waves. 
PS: This beach is specific for Surfing and might be dangerous for regular dips as the waves are very strong.

We stayed in 3 bedroom pool villa and absolutely loved it. The villa was very clean,well maintained , pool was cleaned regularly, kitchen with all vessels was available to cook our own meals.

The soul of these Villas are their AMAZING staff- everyone from security,housekeeping,gardeners,restaurant,buggy drivers keeps greeting us with such a bright smile wholeheartedly and it gives us such a wonderful positive vibes.

As we have been to Bali couple of times before , this trip we just wanted to stay in Villa and rejuvenate. We tried most of their cuisines in Menu and food tasted delicious.
I was surprised that food prices was very low compared to local restaurants we visited couple of times during our stay like Nasi Goreng was just 45k, Nasi Putih - 10k, Ayam Goreng - 60k,grilled Tuna -40k,Mie Goreng - 45k,Melon Juice - 20k

The breakfast timing 07-11 was very suitable for us though the food was cold most of the times but we didnt mind as it was delicious and filling !!! Mr Putu Adi at the restaurant was very caring ,greeting us every morning and when I mentioned my love for local indonesian cuisines , he suggested to order my fav local cuisine at the restaurant even though they are not in the Menu . We did order local cuisines for lunch and thoroughly enjoyed my Capchay, kankung,etc.

We experienced multiple spa messages and it was awesome with prices being very reasonable compared to other places we tried in Bali !!

We have used their Airport pick and drop services and they were very kind to give us a complimentary car service to near by hospital to get our RAT test as it was mandatory for our return flight.
PS: Uber/Gojeck not allowed in this area so you need to rely on their car service if not need to take your own car/bike rental.The resort provides a car with driver and fuel for entire day for only 700k, again very reasonable when compared to elsewhere in Bali.

All in all , a great stay with family and would strongly recommend this place.
title: Highly recommend this beautiful resort

text: For a start, these villas are a good 40 minutes drive from Ubud which was fine with me.  A two minute walk from the beach which has sparkling black sand and some good waves for surfers.  Just make sure you are prepared to drive for evening meals as the beach front restaurant will not be ready until December.  The locals are very friendly and will do anything to help you.  Putu at the local shop is a great one for organising drivers etc at a very good rate.  Security at the villas is great with the guards constantly making checks.  The boys at the Blue Diamond Cafe on the beach make good basic food and are very cheap.  Make sure you bring plenty of cash as the nearest ATM is about 10 mins away in Sukawati.  Come here to relax and have some quality 'down' time.  And an early morning or evening walk along the beach is peaceful and beautiful.

預定當時看餐廳的景很美,實際入住用餐,海灘超級髒,垃圾一堆,餐廳的食物美味,但每天的早餐一成不變,我們預訂了三人分的早餐,五天的早餐,有一天沒有預訂的咖啡,另兩天則少了2分個人份的麵包.
Housekeeping的工作人員訓練,明顯不足以因應客戶的需求,面紙盒內的面紙總是不夠,浴室的廁紙潮濕,感覺很久沒使用,庫存時間太久吸了溼氣的觸感,衛生用品得提醒才會每天補充,被單有污漬.
最不滿意的是交通,奉勸若要直接進住就不出門,其他峇里島的景點全部參觀的旅客,再考慮這一間飯店,因為飯店的地點非常的不好,會讓你花費極為高額的交通費,比如,預訂接機,費用350,000IDR,回程改用KLOOK送機,費用184,000IDR!包了半天4小時的私人司機,費用450,000IDR,當天遇到峇里島祭典,整整空等了1.5小時才回飯店,因為是私人司機,所以若會遇到當地祭典,理應建議其他地點或先回飯店也行,而非空等!單趟去烏布的報價250,000IDR,這些費用飯店回覆是SPECIAL PRICE!好驚人的SPECIAL PRICE!
title: 糟透了!實體和照片有落差的峇里島VILLA

text: A due passi dalla spiaggia di Keramas abbiamo soggiornato in una delle villette con piscina del complesso.. una vera bomba! Ingresso privato, giardino, spazio auto, super piscina, soggiorno con cucina e una splendida camera con bagno annesso. Lo staff è davvero cordiale, sempre disponibile e attento. Il livello di pulizia è alto! C’è un servizio shuttle su richiesta che ti accompagna al ristorante, sito sulla spiaggia, che dista circa 100/150 metri, dipende dove è collocata la "camera". Al ristorante la splendida Mita vi regalerà il sorriso più bello di Bali. Si mangia molto bene e a colazione è possibile mangiare sempre qualcosa di diverso e sempre molto abbondante. Lo raccomandiamo ma soprattutto speriamo di tornarci presto.
title: Un angolo di paradiso

text:
Wunderschöne Villa mit Privatpool! Sehr sauber und mit sehr gutem Personal. Frühstück reichhaltig und à la carte. Somit Hotel insgesamt top!
Man muss sich einfach bewusst sein, dass der Strand nicht zum Baden geeignet ist: hohe Wellen, der schwarze Lavasand wird sehr heiss. Zum Surfen wahrscheinlich super. Vor Ort kann man nicht viel machen, die Anlage liegt zwischen einer Hauptstrasse und dem Meer. Zu empfehlen also, wenn man Tagesausflüge machen möchte oder einfach den Privatpool geniesst. Zum Nachtessen unbedingt ins nahe gelegene Warong Legong mit Abholservice!
title: Schöne Villa, schlechte Lage

text: Старые виллы, с неприятным запахом, требующие срочный ремонт, соседи через забор, как в танхаусах, - всех слышно и видно. Зато рядом пляж! И несколько пляжных кафешек. В целом глушь редкая! Были в вилле на три семьи, бассейн большой, но это единственный плюс. На кухне есть плита, но нет ни одной посуды... Цели готовить у нас не было, но все же... Все грязно, мебель старая, дверцы не держаться ровно, холодильник по типу Минска не размороженный. Сюда ехать, только от безисходности только...
title: Не стоит посещения!!!!

text: Wir buchten eine 3 Bedroom Villa aus der Not heraus, da wir kurzfristig wegen des Erdbebens nicht auf die Gilis konnten. Erst waren wir froh eine schöne Unterkunft zu bekommen.aber dann, naja. Der spontane Pick-up klappte super. Dort angekommen bekamen wir eine 2 Bedroom Villa. Eigentlich kein Problem, wenn es irgendwer bemerkt hätte. Konnte letztendlich geklärt werden und wir konnten weniger bezahlen. Die Villen waren sauber. Im Bad der Mastervilla gibt es jedoch kein Fenster. Dort stank es ekelig.Wir waren 4 Personen, doch es gab nur 2 Sonnenliegen. Eine 3. konnte ergattert werden,, mehr aber nicht. obwohl wenig Gäste da waren.Wir hatten auch nur 1 Handtuch pro Person für Körper, Gesicht und Pool. Auf Nachfrage bekam ich noch ein kleines dazu. Am 3. Tag wurden dann noch Pooltücher gebracht.Ebenso mussten wir mehrmals um Toilettenpaier bitten.Das Frühstück war gut, die Aussicht im Restaurant ist sehr schön. Das ganze Restaurantteam war sehr nett, besonders Miss Saui. Ebenso waren die Mitarbeiter in der Villa sehr freundlich.Die Rollervermietung klappte super. Der Pool war sauber.
title: Naja, hätte mehr erwartet

text: Vriendelijk en behulpzaam personeel. Ontbijt wordt altijd met een mooie glimlach aan de villa gebracht. Het restaurant blijft echter een mysterie! Is het nu open of niet? Soms brandt er licht, vaak geen leven te bespeuren! Gelukkig was er een hippe bar aan het zwarte strand ernaast; héérlijk gegeten hier, elke keer opnieuw. Komune Beach Resort; place to be. Hier dineer je met de donderende golven als live tv! Zee is niet geschikt om in te zwemmen; rotsen, koraal, sterke branding en metershoge golven! Afschuwelijk al dat afval op het strand. Had ervan gelezen en het is ook effectief zo! Wees gewaarschuwd! Hier ligt dan ook niemand te zonnen buiten een verdwaald koppel toeristen. Betere plek om te zonnen is Blue Lagoon in Padangbai. Leuk snorkelen daar! Keramas is wel een goede uitvalsbasis om Oost-Bali te verkennen. Goedkoper dan Nusa Dua, Sanur en Kuta. Heel rustige en immense villa's voor max 6 personen. Elk met eigen kamer en badkamer: super!
title: Mooi complex van privé villa's op wandelafstand van het strand.

text: Dit appartementencomplex is bijzonder mooi ingericht en heeft hele goede service. Ik ben hier samen met mijn vriendin in januari 2013 een week geweest en we hebben het prima naar onze zin gehad. Het strand is op 5 minuten afstand en je hebt een eigen prive zwembad in de tuin. De tuin is mooi met tropische planten en in het huis heb je alles wat nodig is om er een fijne vakantie van te maken, inclusief ruime en volledig geoutilleerde keuken. Het geheel is bijzonder smaakvol ontworpen. Kortom: een aanrader!
title: Uitstekend verblijf dichtbij surfstrand
